Re: 怖くないと。。。。?
by Snowflake » Thu 06.10.2010 12:42 pm Going ever-so-slightly off topic here (sorry), but with the word "sigaret" are you going for the English word "cigarette"? When I read your first post, I thought a "sigaret" might be some sort of Japanese funeral ritual item that is lit to honor the dead.I wish I could provide guidance on your original question (the significance of と in the example), but I'm so much of a beginner I wouldn't have even known enough to ask the question. Now I'm curious to know the answer.
